shiftCdrTab
Class PatrolAssignment

java.lang.Object
  shiftCdrTab.PatrolAssignment

public class PatrolAssignment
extends java.lang.Object

The PatrolAssignment class represents a patrol route that may be assigned to an officer. This is a very simple class containing only one variable, the name of the assignment. A PatrolAssignment object is created from the patrolsList.xml file. PatrolAssignment objects are used by the OfficerAssignment class to assign a particular patrol route to an officer. Each OfficerAssignment contains at least one, if not more PatrolAssignments. A single PatrolAssignment may be assigned to zero or more officers. Both Supervisors and Shift Commanders can create new patrol routes to be permanently added to the patrolsList.xml or temporary patrol routes to be used one time only. Both kinds of patrol routes are identically represented by PatrolAssignment objects.

See Also:
OfficerAssignment, ShiftCdrReport

setTimePatroled

public void setTimePatroled(java.lang.String timePatroled)
Sets the timePatroled value which specifies the time range the patrol route was patrolled. This value should be pre-formated into the desired 'HH:mm - HH:mm' format before being passed into this method.
Note It is the responsibility of the caller to ensure the value passed to this method is pre-formated to match the 'HH:mm - HH:mm' format. This method does not employ any checks to prevent timePatroled from being set to Strings not matching this format.

Parameters:
timePatroled - - the pre-formated time range the patrol route was patrolled
format = 'HH:mm - HH:mm' where HH represents the hour given in 24 hour format (12am/midnight = 00)
